01:46:16.900 --> 01:46:25.210
So in a simpler
situation, you just

01:46:25.210 --> 01:46:27.740
don't turn on any operator.

01:46:27.740 --> 01:46:32.199
You just take phi equal to 0.

01:46:32.199 --> 01:46:33.490
So this is a simpler situation.

01:46:33.490 --> 01:46:36.870
Then you just have the
partition function.

01:46:36.870 --> 01:46:39.500
So this correlation function is
defined by the Euclidean path

01:46:39.500 --> 01:46:41.067
integral, for example.

01:46:41.067 --> 01:46:43.400
And you just insert this in
the Euclidean path integral.

01:46:46.412 --> 01:46:48.870
And when phi is equal to 0,
this is just the Euclidean path

01:46:48.870 --> 01:46:51.242
integral.

01:46:51.242 --> 01:46:53.200
And this is just gives
you a partition function

01:46:53.200 --> 01:46:56.580
of the whole system.

01:46:56.580 --> 01:47:00.470
And since we believe
the duality should be 2,

01:47:00.470 --> 01:47:02.090
then this partition
function should

01:47:02.090 --> 01:47:03.360
be exactly the same
as the partition

01:47:03.360 --> 01:47:04.568
function on the gravity side.

01:47:08.199 --> 01:47:09.740
Suppose you can
compute the partition

01:47:09.740 --> 01:47:11.079
function from the gravity side.

01:47:11.079 --> 01:47:12.120
Then it must be the same.

01:47:12.120 --> 01:47:15.820
Otherwise, there's
no equivalence.

01:47:15.820 --> 01:47:18.150
So this is the partition
function of the gravity side.

01:47:26.280 --> 01:47:28.830
So these have to be true.

01:47:28.830 --> 01:47:42.830
So now, with this
relation, again, we

01:47:42.830 --> 01:47:46.340
are right in the heuristic
form that some operator O

01:47:46.340 --> 01:47:50.820
is due to some [INAUDIBLE] phi.

01:47:50.820 --> 01:47:56.180
And the source for the O is due
to the boundary value of phi--

01:47:56.180 --> 01:47:58.382
again, I write in
the heuristic form.

01:47:58.382 --> 01:47:59.840
So the boundary
value of phi should

01:47:59.840 --> 01:48:01.300
be understood in that limit.

01:48:04.810 --> 01:48:08.760
Because of this,
then that means we

01:48:08.760 --> 01:48:19.730
must have-- if we turn on
a [INAUDIBLE] or a phi,

01:48:19.730 --> 01:48:22.480
deforming the
series by this phi,

01:48:22.480 --> 01:48:25.890
the mass corresponding to the
gravity side of the partition

01:48:25.890 --> 01:48:33.460
function, with this phi,
have the boundary value

01:48:33.460 --> 01:48:36.370
given by phi.

01:48:36.370 --> 01:48:44.720
Then it must be the same
because we have identified

01:48:44.720 --> 01:48:48.770
turning on the boundary value
to turning on the operator,

01:48:48.770 --> 01:48:53.660
turning on this thing
in the field series.

01:48:53.660 --> 01:48:58.880
So we have now
related the generating

01:48:58.880 --> 01:49:04.450
functional to the
gravity partition

01:49:04.450 --> 01:49:06.430
function with some
non-normalizable boundary

01:49:06.430 --> 01:49:06.930
conditions.

01:49:16.220 --> 01:49:25.370
