01:50:04.260 --> 01:50:09.270
So in this limit,
we can just write

01:50:09.270 --> 01:50:14.060
the gravity path in
function, essentially

01:50:14.060 --> 01:50:16.812
as the Euclidean path integral
of all gravity fields.

01:50:19.860 --> 01:50:21.750
Again, I'm using
this heuristic form

01:50:21.750 --> 01:50:23.083
to write the boundary condition.

01:50:23.083 --> 01:50:25.135
But it should be
understood in that form.

01:50:27.820 --> 01:50:31.520
And again, I'm by
integrating over phi,

01:50:31.520 --> 01:50:34.354
